14	Pretérito Imperfecto de Indicativo	<p>The <strong>Pret&eacute;rito Imperfecto de Indicativo</strong> is one of the past tenses in Spanish. It is used to describe ongoing or habitual actions in the past, provide background information, or describe things as they were.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4>Uses of Pret&eacute;rito Imperfecto</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li><strong>Habitual Actions:</strong> Actions that happened regularly in the past.\r\n\r\n\t<div class="example">Example: &quot;Cuando era ni&ntilde;o, <em>jugaba</em> en el parque todos los d&iacute;as.&quot; (When I was a child, I used to play in the park every day.)</div>\r\n\t</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Descriptions:</strong> To describe people, places, or situations in the past.\r\n\t<div class="example">Example: &quot;La casa <em>era</em> grande y <em>ten&iacute;a</em> un jard&iacute;n hermoso.&quot; (The house was big and had a beautiful garden.)</div>\r\n\t</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Ongoing Actions:</strong> Actions that were happening at a particular time in the past.\r\n\t<div class="example">Example: &quot;Yo <em>le&iacute;a</em> un libro mientras ella <em>escuchaba</em> m&uacute;sica.&quot; (I was reading a book while she was listening to music.)</div>\r\n\t</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4>Conjugation of Regular Verbs</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The following table shows the conjugation of regular verbs in the imperfect tense:</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n\t<thead>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<th>Pronoun</th>\r\n\t\t\t<th>-AR Verbs (Hablar)</th>\r\n\t\t\t<th>-ER Verbs (Comer)</th>\r\n\t\t\t<th>-IR Verbs (Vivir)</th>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t</thead>\r\n\t<tbody>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td>Yo</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td>hablaba</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td>com&iacute;a</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td>viv&iacute;a</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td>T&uacute;</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td>hablabas</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td>com&iacute;as</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td>viv&iacute;as</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td>&Eacute;l/Ella/Uste