18	El verbo "LLEVAR"	<p>The verb <strong>&quot;llevar&quot;</strong> is highly versatile in Spanish and is used in a variety of contexts. It generally means &quot;to carry&quot; or &quot;to take,&quot; but its meaning changes depending on the situation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Meanings and Uses of &quot;Llevar&quot;</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>1. To Carry or Transport</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Llevar&quot; is used to indicate carrying or transporting something or someone from one place to another.</p>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Example:</strong> &quot;Siempre <em>llevo</em> una botella de agua en mi mochila.&quot; (I always carry a water bottle in my backpack.)</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>2. To Wear (Clothing or Accessories)</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>It is used to describe what someone is wearing.</p>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Example:</strong> &quot;Hoy <em>llevo</em> una camiseta roja.&quot; (Today I&rsquo;m wearing a red t-shirt.)</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>3. To Take (Someone or Something Somewhere)</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Llevar&quot; can mean to take someone or something to a specific location.</p>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Example:</strong> &quot;&iquest;Puedes <em>llevar</em> estos documentos a la oficina?&quot; (Can you take these documents to the office?)</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>4. To Indicate Duration or Progress</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>It can be used to describe how long someone has been doing something.</p>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Example:</strong> &quot;Llevo tres a&ntilde;os aprendiendo espa&ntilde;ol.&quot; (I&rsquo;ve been learning Spanish for three years.)</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>5. To Indicate Superiority or Advantage</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Llevar&quot; can express that someone is ahead of or superior to another in some way.</p>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Example:</strong> &quot;Ella me <em>lleva</em> dos puntos en el examen.&quot; (She is two points ahead of me in the exam.)</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>6. To Handle or Manage</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>It is used to indicate managing or handling a task or responsibility.</p>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Example:</strong> &quot;Mi hermana <em>lleva</em> la contabilidad de la empresa.&quot; (My sister manages the company&rsquo;s accounting.)</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Conjugation of &quot;Llevar&quot; in Present Tense</h4>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n\t<thead>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<th>Pronoun</th>\r\n\t\t\t<th>Conjugation</th>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t</thead>\r\n\t<tbody>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td>Yo</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td>llevo</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td>T&uacute;</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td>llevas</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td>&Eacute;l/Ella/Usted</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td>lleva</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td>Nosotros/as</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td>llevamos</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td>Vosotros/as</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td>llev&aacute;is</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td>Ellos/Ellas/Ustedes</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td>llevan</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4>Common Expressions with &quot;Llevar&quot;</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li><strong>&quot;Llevar algo puesto&quot;:</strong> To wear something.\r\n\r\n\t<div><strong>Example:</strong> &quot;&iquest;Qu&eacute; ropa <em>llevas</em> hoy?&quot; (What clothes are you wearing today?)</div>\r\n\t</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li><strong>&quot;Llevar tiempo haciendo algo&quot;:</strong> To have been doing something for a certain amount of time.\r\n\r\n\t<div><strong>Example:</strong> &quot;Llevo dos horas esperando.&quot; (I&rsquo;ve been waiting for two hours.)</div>\r\n\t</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li><strong>&quot;Llevar ventaja&quot;:</strong> To have an advantage or lead.\r\n\r\n\t<div><strong>Example:</strong> &quot;Tu equipo <em>lleva</em> tres puntos de ventaja.&quot; (Your team is three points ahead.)</div>\r\n\t</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li><strong>&quot;Llevarse bien/mal&quot;:</strong> To get along well/poorly with someone.\r\n\r\n\t<div><strong>Example:</strong> &quot;Ellos se <em>llevan</em> muy bien.&quot; (They get along very well.)</div>\r\n\t</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4>Practice Exercises</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Complete the sentences with the correct form of &quot;llevar&quot;:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>Yo siempre (llevar) __________ una agenda conmigo.</li>\r\n\t<li>Ellos (llevar) __________ tres a&ntilde;os trabajando juntos.</li>\r\n\t<li>Nosotros (llevar) __________ a los ni&ntilde;os al colegio todas las ma&ntilde;anas.</li>\r\n\t<li>&iquest;Qu&eacute; ropa (llevar) __________ t&uacute; para la fiesta?</li>\r\n\t<li>Mi hermano y yo nos (llevar) __________ bien.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<div class="see-answers">\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="see-answers"><input id="toggle-answers" type="checkbox" /> <label class="toggle-label" for="toggle-answers"><strong>Answers</strong></label>\r\n\r\n<ol class="answers-list">\r\n\t<li>llevo</li>\r\n\t<li>llevan</li>\r\n\t<li>llevamos</li>\r\n\t<li>llevas</li>\r\n\t<li>llevamos</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4>Conclusion</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The verb &quot;llevar&quot; is incredibly versatile and essential for daily communication in Spanish. By practicing its various meanings and uses, you can enhance your fluency and expressiveness in Spanish.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>		2024-12-01 12:00:00.194313+00	2024-12-02 12:44:49.779868+00	2	el-verbo-llevar
